ality.  For those that stay at the higher levels are those that love playing a paladin (I'm one of these too), and can't think of another class which we have so much fun playing.  In closing, so what if druids are moving into our quest for the Ghoulbane, eventually it'll be worth about 100pp and they will stop.  Becuase there are far more easier things to do to get 100pp in an hours work.  I actually make that much now in just a regular hunting group, they will eventually head back to their little area in Rathe Mountains and kill their Hill Giants for 30pp per kill soon enough.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Dadin <br>54th Cavalier<br>Honored Circle on Xev<br><br>Dwarven Thane<br>Hellwinds - Palomides </td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
